        "content": "<p>Hi,<br>\nI was wondering if there is a formal connection between limits in the categorical sense, and the \"traditional\" limits of function/sequence. <br>\nI get that the limit can be seen as a lower upper bound in case of ordered elements, but to me it seems like a specific case of limit.</p>",
        "id": 244860013,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincent L",
        "timestamp": 1625405947
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"399982\">@Vincent L</span> See <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/questions/9951/limits-in-category-theory-and-analysis\">this</a>.</p>",
        "id": 244861486,
        "sender_full_name": "সায়ন্তন রায়",
        "timestamp": 1625408259
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>thank you</p>",
        "id": 244862098,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincent L",
        "timestamp": 1625409219
